    "updated_at": "2025-02-23T21:02:18Z",
    "body": "I found an workaround. Forcing pseudo-terminal allocation allows me to run fish+starship with ssh.\n```\nssh -t desktop fish \n```\nor if you add `RequestTTY force` to  ssh_config it will work without `-t`\n\n```\nHost desktop\n  User osbm\n  HostName 192.168.0.1\n  IdentityFile [identity file path]\n  RemoteCommand fish\n  RequestTTY force\n```",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
